We further performed a simulation study to investigate the effect of imputation on genome-wide association mapping. Heritability was set again to 0.91. Simulation was performed assuming one QTL explaining 10% of the genetic variance for which a perfect marker was available in the 90 k, but not in the 9 k SNP array. The remaining 9,925 markers were assumed to contribute equally (i.e., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
